Label: Domain
Definition: Generally, land and water owned by individuals or corporations as opposed to the state; in French civil law, any government property capable of being owned by non-public entities, which cannot be seized and which is restricted to the stipulated ownership and use.

Label: e-nose
Definition: An electronic nose is an electronic sensing device intended to detect odors or flavors. The expression "electronic sensing" refers to the capability of reproducing human senses using sensor arrays and pattern recognition systems.

Label: FTIR
Definition: An FTIR sensor is a device that uses Fourier-transform infrared spectroscopy (FTIR) technology to detect and analyze the infrared absorption spectra of various substances. Fourier Transform Infrared (FTIR) analysis is a spectroscopic technique that makes use of the naturally occurring electromagnetic spectrum defined by the wavelengths between 2,500nm and 25,000nm.

Label: FreshDetect
Definition: FreshDetect is a German company engaged in the manufacturing and supply of handheld sensors for analyzing microbiological quality to determine the freshness of meat and other food products in real time.

Label: HPLC
Definition: An HPLC sensor is a device that is used in conjunction with a high-performance liquid chromatography (HPLC) system to detect and measure the concentration of various chemical compounds in a sample.

Label: MSI
Definition: Multispectral imaging (MSI) is the system that involves capturing images of a scene or object over multiple discrete wavelength bands and extracting spectral content from that data.

Label: NIR
Definition: Near Infrared, or NIR, spectroscopy is an analysis technique for fast, accurate food testing. NIR measurement is a widely-used method in the food and drink and agricultural industries, and it is a convenient, low cost alternative to chemical analysis.

Label: GCMS
Definition: Combination of Gas Chromatography and Mass Spectrometry. A mass spectrometer is typically utilized in one of two ways: full scan or selective ion monitoring (SIM). The typical GC-MS instrument is capable of performing both functions either individually or concomitantly, depending on the setup of the particular instrument (Sounds like a parameter to supply). The columns represent for certain substances. As such, they are mappable to concepts (as opposed to the spectra where column headers are potentially infinite).

Label: FTIR-6200
Definition: The FT/IR-6200 is a Fourier Transform Infrared Spectrometer manufactured by the company JASCO. It is a high-performance research-grade spectrometer that is used for the analysis of various samples in chemistry, materials science, and biology.
name: rdfs:Literal

Label: Fox3000
Definition: The FOX3000 e-nose device is an electronic nose system developed by Alpha MOS. The Fox 3000 provides either 12 sensors of same technology or 12 sensors of different type.

Label: FreshDetectBFD-100
Definition: BFD-100 is a handheld sensor of FreshDetect company. It is capable of determining bacterial contamination in pork in real time using a non-invasive, fluorescence spectroscopy measurement technique. This handheld device can be used to determine the total viable count in fresh meat in 3â€“5 seconds with laboratory quality reliability and accuracy.

Label: hasLocation
Definition: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

Label: hasLatitude
Definition: The latitude of a location. For example 37.42242 (WGS 84).

Label: hasLongitude
Definition: The longitude of a location. For example -122.08585 (WGS 84).

Label: hasAddress
Definition: The address of an geographical entity, for example, address of an organization

Label: Measurement
Definition: Represents the measured value made over a property. It is also linked to the unit of measure in which the value is expressed and the timestamp of the measurement.

Label: UnitOfMeasure
Definition: The unit of measure is a standard for measurement of a quantity, such as a Property. For example, Power is a property and Watt is a unit of power that represents a definite predetermined power: when we say 10 Watt, we actually mean 10 times the definite predetermined power called "watt".

Label: isResultOf
Definition: Relation linking a Result to the Experiment that created or caused it.

Label: hasResult
Definition: Relation linking an Observation and a Sensor or Actuator and a Result, which contains a value representing the value associated with the observed Property.

Label: ProcessInvolved
Definition: Relation linking a process to the entities that are involved in that process.

Label: conductsExperimentsIn
Definition: Relation linking an experiment to the location where it is conducted.

Label: hasSample
Definition: Relation between a Dataset and the Sample used to represent it.

Label: isSampleOf
Definition: Relation from a Sample to the Dataset that it is intended to be representative of.

Label: hasSampleType
Definition: Relation linking a sample to its type

Label: isCollectedFrom
Definition: Relation linking a sample to the entity or location from which it was collected

Label: isPerformedAt
Definition: Relation linking an activity to the location where it is performed

Label: isPerformedOn
Definition: Relation linking an activity to the object or material on which it is performed

Label: hasMeasurement
Definition: A relationship between a feature of interest and a measurement about it

Label: hasProperty
Definition: A relationship between a feature of interest and a property of that feature

Label: hasSensorType
Definition: A relationship identifying the type of a sensor in a device (i.e., Enose, HPLC, MSI, etc.)

Label: isPropertyOf
Definition: A relationship between a property and the feature of interest it belongs to

Label: measuresProperty
Definition: A relationship specifying the property that can be measured by a certain device

Label: relatesToMeasurement
Definition: A relationship between a property and the measurements it relates to

Label: isControlledByDevice
Definition: A relationship specifying the devices that can control a certain property

Label: isMeasuredByDevice
Definition: A relationship specifying the devices that can measure a certain property

Label: isMeasuredIn
Definition: A relationship identifying the unit of measure used for a certain entity.

Label: isMeasurementOf
Definition: A relationship between a measurement and the feature of interest whose quality was measured

Label: makesMeasurement
Definition: A relation between a device and the measurements it makes. Such measurement will link together the value of the measurement, its unit of measure and the property to which it relates.

Label: relatesToProperty
Definition: A relationship between a measurement and the property it relates to

Label: detectProperty
Definition: A relationship represent properties detected by a sensor

Label: base_name
Definition: A data property that represents the fundamental or primary name of an entity

Label: base_value
Definition: A data property that specifies a numerical or categorical value that serves as a reference point or standard for a given entity or property

Label: has_value
Definition: A relationship defining the value of a certain property, e.g., energy or power

Label: has_version
Definition: A relationship defining the version of a certain entity, e.g: device, etc

Label: name
Definition: The name of the item.

Label: time
Definition: A data property that represents the time when a sample was storaged

Label: update_time
Definition: A data property that represents the date and time when an entity was last updated or modified.

Label: hasAdditionalID
Definition: A data property that represents the additional sample identifier

Label: hasBatchNumber
Definition: A data property that represent the batch number of a sample

Label: hasTemperature
Definition: A data property that represents the storage temperature of a sample

Label: hasSampleId
Definition: A data property that represents the ID of a sample
